title: Episode 18 (LIVE): Celebrating Student Research
itunes:author: UW-Green Bay Psychology Department
itunes:summary: Drs. Gurung and Martin chat with six different students about their research on topics related to death, moral decision making, autism, cultural competence, and suicide.  These six students (Liza Steffeck, Sarah Busko, Chad Osteen, Vince Badalamenti, Michelle McChesney, and Will Vogt) represent just a few of the more than 40 UWGB Psychology students who will be presenting their work at Posters in the Rotunda, the Midwestern Psychological Association Conference, and the UWGB Academic Excellence Symposium.
